{
  "analysis": "The current /app/mystery.c is an incorrect guessed raytracer (verified md5 a36bc6586fa014f9e174053d77d88f53 vs required e866fa2c851f4a9da736b4ed3ba3912e). It outputs near-black first pixels while the original starts with sky. We need exact reconstruction from disassembly before writing another implementation. The next concrete step is to dump helper functions (vector_normalize, sphere_intersect, allocate_image) and main inner-loop chunks, plus symbol addresses, to identify exact camera/ray/scene/shading logic.",
